A nurse spoke to Masego Rahlaga on condition of anonymity. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - What would you do if one day – while you were at work – the building caught fire? Panic perhaps? READ: Charlotte Maxeke Hospital reeling after weekend blaze Well, a nurse who works at the Charlotte Maxeke Academic Hospital in Johannesburg has described her calm in the midst of a storm the day the facility caught fire. The blaze could only be extinguished after 24 hours. * eNCA's Masego Rahlaga reports.